Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni, has approved the appointments of seven permanent secretaries into the state civil service. This was made known in a statement signed by the State Head of Service, Mohammed Nura, and obtained by DAILY POST on Thursday. The newly appointed permanent secretaries are; Usman A Bura; Ali Mustafa; Ajiya A. Musa; Audu Umaru; Abdullahi Abba; Isa Bukar and Hamidu Isa Babi The statement added that, the appointments are with immediate effect.